The optimization process using Response Surface Methodology (RSM) largely involves three distinct steps: Generation of statistically designed experimental designs, co-efficient estimation using mathematical modelling, and lastly, response prediction and testing of the significance of the model to the experiment38. The experimental design was generated using the Box Behnken Design (BBD) RSM models using the Design Expert 11 software (StatEase, 2020). The optimization formula used was as shown in Eq. 1 39. The parameters considered for optimization were a reduction in the fungal load and a percent reduction in the aflatoxin content. The variable factors were time, pressure and ionization power.1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
